.TH "i40e_read_nvm_buffer" 9 "i40e_read_nvm_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_read_nvm_buffer \- Reads Shadow RAM buffer and acquire lock if necessary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "i40e_status" i40e_read_nvm_buffer
.BI "(struct i40e_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 offset "  ","
.BI "u16 *words "  ","
.BI "u16 *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "offset" 12
offset of the Shadow RAM word to read (0x000000 - 0x001FFF).
.IP "words" 12
(in) number of words to read; (out) number of words actually read
.IP "data" 12
words read from the Shadow RAM
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads 16 bit words (data buffer) from the SR using the \fBi40e_read_nvm_srrd\fP
method. The buffer read is preceded by the NVM ownership take
and followed by the release.
